#Approach:

3Sum – Sorting + Two Pointer Approach

Sabse pehle array ko sort karte hain.
Phir har element ko ek fixed element maan kar baaki do elements two pointer se find karte hain.

Ek loop se i fix karo.
Uske baad j = i+1 aur k = n-1 rakho.

Ab sum = nums[i] + nums[j] + nums[k] calculate karo:
Agar sum 0 se chhota hai, to j++ karo taki sum bada ho.
Agar sum 0 se bada hai, to k-- karo taki sum chhota ho.
Agar sum 0 hai, to triplet mil gaya, usse answer me add karo.

Duplicate triplets avoid karne ke liye:
same i ko skip karo
aur triplet milne ke baad same j aur same k values ko bhi skip karo.

Is tarah unique triplets mil jate hain jinka sum 0 hota hai.

Time Complexity: O(n^2)
Space Complexity: O(1) extra space (excluding output)

#Code:

class Solution {
    public List<List<Integer>> threeSum(int[] nums) {
        List<List<Integer>> ans = new ArrayList<>();

        Arrays.sort(nums);
        int n = nums.length;

        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            if(i > 0 && nums[i] == nums[i-1]){
                continue;
            }

            int j = i+1;
            int k = n-1;

            while(j < k){
                int sum = nums[i] + nums[j] + nums[k];
                if(sum < 0){
                    j++;
                }
                else if(sum > 0){
                    k--;
                }
                else{
                    List<Integer> temp = new ArrayList<>();
                    temp.add(nums[i]);
                    temp.add(nums[j]);
                    temp.add(nums[k]);

                    ans.add(temp);

                    j++;
                    k--;
                    while(j < k && nums[j] == nums[j-1]) j++;
                    while(j < k && nums[k] == nums[k+1]) k--;
                }
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
}
